Our Solution: Hemora

An intelligent, agentic AI-powered blood bank management system that predicts, monitors, and autonomously acts to prevent shortage and wastage.

THE PROBLEMS FACED:

A. Blood Shortages
-Why: Hospitals don‚Äôt know in real-time which blood groups are available; sudden emergencies cause shortages.
-Impact: Patients in critical condition may not get timely transfusions.

B. Blood Wastage
-Why: Blood has a shelf life of 30‚Äì42 days. Expiry isn‚Äôt tracked effectively, and transportation/redistribution is poor.
-Impact: Millions of units go unused each year, despite demand elsewhere.

C. Manual, Fragmented Systems
-Why: Many hospitals still maintain paper logs or disconnected digital records.
-Impact: Hard to coordinate stock between hospitals, predict demand, or respond to emergencies.

D. Hospitals lack predictive foresight‚Äîthey react to shortages instead of preventing them

THE ROOT CAUSE:

-No real-time visibility into blood inventory across departments
-Manual tracking leads to delayed alerts for expiring units
-Zero predictive capability for upcoming demand (surgeries, accidents, seasonal trends)
-No coordination between blood banks, leading to simultaneous shortages and wastage

(The human cost? Preventable deaths, surgery delays, and wasted donor blood that could have saved lives.)

HOW AI CAN SOLVE THESE PROBLEMS:

A. Real-Time Inventory Monitoring
-AI Role: Track blood units in each hospital automatically.
-How: Scans updates from inventory dashboards
Highlights low stock and near-expiry units
-Impact: Immediate alerts prevent shortages and wastage.

B. Predictive Demand Analytics
-AI Role: Forecast blood demand for each blood group.
-How: Analyze historical usage, seasonal patterns, and hospital-specific trends
Predict units likely needed over next 7‚Äì14 days
-Impact: Hospitals can proactively prepare donation drives and manage stock.

C. Automated Alerts and Action Recommendations
-AI Role: Act as a 24/7 intelligent assistant.
-How : Sends alerts for low stock or expiry
Suggests blood donation drives

D. Inter-Hospital Coordination (Future Phase)
-AI Role: Network multiple hospitals for optimal redistribution.
-How : Detect surplus in one hospital and shortage in another
Suggest or automate transfers to prevent both wastage and shortages
-Impact: Efficient utilization of blood resources across regions.

